(355, 67, 'Here are a couple of notes:\r\n\r\n1)	You reference $node[0] in a function where $node may not be in scope.\r\n2)	I believe the machineType value is Fortinet, Inc. not plain Fortinet (see some of the existing tickets created by Network Monitoring user to confirm this)\r\n3)	I would update the Standard Network Monitoring ticket title to use just the first part of the node name, not the entire thing (ie $node[0] from the main function. For Fortinet tickets, I think it makes sense to leave the entire node name in it, as you have it currently.\r\n\r\nBefore you commit it, you should do a bit of testing in dev to make sure you are confident it does what you expect. You could do this by writing a side script that hits the API using the curl utility with post variables set to mock up the solar winds alert requests. Or you can just hit the url in a browser with GET variables set to mock up the solar winds data. When you get to a point when you want to test, I can help you out if you like. It may help to briefly write out what scenarios you would like to test.\r\n'),
