(415, 91, 'The purpose of this document is to define a requirement for a new trigger for the TACACS Disconnect Task (Task Template 542) in ITC. \r\n\r\nThe TACACS Disconnect Task is used during the automated disconnect process.  It was originally triggered every time a circuit was cancelled.  Greg Drake from the NOC has stated that the actual requirement for this task to be triggered is when a client cancels all their services.\r\n\r\nThe original trigger has been deleted from ITC. \r\n\r\nA single TACACS Disconnect Task should be triggered when a Cancel SA contains all the billing services for a client. \r\n\r\nThe trigger for the Circuit Disconnect Task does not need to be changed. '),
(416, 90, 'Alogithm:  Remaining Term\r\n\r\nexcel: =($B$6*365)-($B$8-C12)\r\npsuedo code: ((Contract term years) * 365)-((CTP as of DATE) -(AccessBillableDateVoice Date))\r\n'),
(417, 90, 'Algorithm: Total CTP\r\n\r\nexcel: =(E12/30)*$B$7*D12\r\n\r\npseudo code: (MRCfromInvoice/30)* (CTP % per contact) * Remaining Term'),
