(351, 67, 'New set of questions :\r\n\r\n1) will &quot;Fortinet&quot; machine types ALWAYS have the node segment -fgt- in it ?\r\nI hope so because this would be fairly easy.\r\n\r\n2) By &quot;these devices will pass the variable that contains &quot; the &quot;MachineType&quot;...\r\n    Does that mean:\r\n	A) I''m supposed to pass the &quot;machine type&quot; to be saved in the tickets table?\r\n	OR\r\n	B) I''m supposed to use this variable to differentiate the 2 machine types. And if so...\r\n	I don''t see a way to do this based on the existing code and data.\r\n	\r\nSummary:\r\nThe way I see it is that based on the &quot;problem_description&quot; field , the type can NOT be differentiated by a varaible of &quot;Fortinet&quot; or &quot;Cisco&quot;, it has to be based on something in the NODE string or based on a different field in the tickets table all together. And I don''t currently see a field that represents the &quot;machine type&quot;.'),
