(370, 78, 'The purpose of this document is to define the requirements of the Professional Services department related to reporting their time in the Timesheet section of MaxxPoint. \r\n\r\nTheir requirement is for projects with the status of Closed or Cancelled to not be presented to them in the Project Dropdowns in the Add Task to Timesheet section of the application. The attached screen shot illustrates a current project drop down list for Joe Welch. He reports that nearly all of the listed projects are closed. \r\n\r\nNo change to the functionality of the system is required. The only requested change is to list only active projects in the Project drop down menu. \r\n\r\nThe status of the projects is listed on the Projects page within MaxxPoint. Please see the following link and attached screen shot: https://maxxpoint.smoothstone.com/boss/prof-serv_projects \r\n\r\nThe available options for Status are: \r\n\r\n Cancelled \r\n\r\n Closed \r\n\r\n Not Started \r\n\r\n Open \r\n\r\n Paused \r\n\r\nThe Project Drop Down menu on the Add Task to Timesheet page should only be populated with projects with a status of Not Started, Open or Paused. Projects with a status of Cancelled or Closed should not have time charged to them and should not be listed in the Drop Down menu. '),
