(390, 81, '2830===============================================================================\r\nBusiness Case:\r\n\r\nAs part of our circuit process we purposely leave tickets open for 24 hours to ensure that an issue is fully resolved after a repair has been made.   This causes us to have to assign a team member to review and manually close each circuit ticket 24 hours after the repair.  The goal of this feature request is gain efficiency by allowing the tickets to auto close after 24 hours has passed.  This will allow us to use our human resources for other tasks.  In June of 2014 the NOC processed over 1700 incident circuit tickets.   Most all of these tickets had to be re-touched and closed 24 hours after a repair was made.\r\n\r\nFeature Request:\r\n\r\nWe would like to add an Auto Close drop down to the State Field in ITC.  Once this field is chosen we would like the following actions to take place:\r\n\r\n         Prompt the user to enter the cause code information. (The same way ITC does currently when an incident ticket is being closed)\r\n         Place a viewable update in the ticket that states:  The incident has been resolved and we will continue to monitor the ticket for an additional 24 hours.  If no additional trouble is identified then the ticket will close after 24 hours. \r\n         Set the ticket action to OPS - Pending Auto Close\r\n         After 24 hours have passed set the ticket to closed and place in the following viewable update:  Ticket XXXXX is now closed.  If you need additional assistance please contact our Network Operations Center at 888-728-0950.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nIf the ticket is updated during the 24 hour while we are waiting for it to age out then we would like the ticket state to set back to active so the ticket will remain open.  We would also like the ticket action to change to OPS  Auto Close Cancelled.  Please note that we will have to create this ticket action but can do it on the fly.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPlease see the attached requirements document dated 072514 with screen shot.  '),
(391, 82, '2826\r\n\r\nThe purpose of this document is to define the requirements of the Solution Management Department related to providing clients (with Admin Level Access only) the capability to request a location cancellation from MaxxPoint.\r\n\r\nThe users request that a new icon be added to the Service Request Dashlet for Location Cancelation to the right of the Service Change icon. \r\n\r\n\r\nOnce users select this icon they should be taken to a page in MaxxPoint that allows them to select what locations they wish to cancel from a list of their active locations.  The client should also be able to check a box to signify a partial cancellation.  It these cases, they should be provided a text box so they can spell out what services will need to be cancelled.  A mockup of the screen is below:\r\n\r\nThis information should then be entered into a new ITC ticket with a problem type and subtype of Service Cancellation assigned to the Coordinator, Solution user who will then complete the Cancel SA for the client.  \r\n'),
(392, 83, '2614\r\n\r\nI would like to make the following changes to the front page dashboard in ITC for the ''NOC'' access template. \r\n\r\nRemove the following: \r\n\r\nTotal # of open TTU Tickets \r\n\r\nTotal # of Open Incident Circuit-Chronic tickets (This subtype is going away as soon as we roll out our automation) \r\n\r\nTotal # of Service changes open and older than 24 hours for NOC \r\n\r\nTotal # of incidents open and older than 72 hours for the NOC \r\n\r\nTotal# of incidents older than 24 hours not in ENG Queue \r\n\r\nAdd the following: \r\n\r\nTotal # of P1 circuits tickets - (All Open tickets with a problem type of incident and a problem subtype of circuit with a priority of 1) \r\n\r\nTotal # of P2 circuits tickets - (All Open tickets with a problem type of incident and a problem subtype of circuit with a priority of 2) \r\n\r\nTotal # of P3 circuits tickets - (All Open tickets with a problem type of incident and a problem subtype of circuit with a priority of 3) \r\n\r\nTotal# of non-circuit P1 Incident tickets - (All Open tickets with a problem type of incident, exclude tickets with the problem problem subtype of circuit only show tickets with a priority of 1) \r\n\r\nTotal # of non-circuit P2 Incident tickets - (All Open tickets with a problem type of incident, exclude tickets with the problem subtype of circuit only show tickets with a priority of 2) \r\n\r\nTotal# of non-circuit P3 incident tickets - (All Open tickets with a problem type of incident, exclude tickets with the problem subtype of circuit only show tickets with a priority of 3) \r\n\r\n\r\nTotal# of Service changes assigned to NOC (All open tickets with a problem type of Service Change that are assigned to a user with a support type of IE, NOT1, or NOT2) \r\n\r\nTotal# of Service changes assigned to VOC (All open tickets with a problem type of Service Change that are assigned to a user with a support type of VCHA, VINC, VOT1, VOT2, or VTKT) \r\n\r\nTotal # of incidents assigned to the NOC (All open tickets with a problem type of Incident that are assigned to a user with a support type of IE, NOT1, or NOT2) \r\n\r\nTotal # of incidents assigned to the VOC All open tickets with a problem type of Incident that are assigned to a user with a support type of VCHA, VINC, VOT1, VOT2, or VTKT) \r\n\r\nTotal# of tickets assigned to VOT2 (All open tickets that are assigned to a user with a support type of VOT2) \r\n\r\nTotal# of tickets assigned to NOT2 (All open tickets that are assigned to a user with a support type of NOT2) \r\n\r\nTotal# of tickets assigned to NOT3 (All open tickets that are assigned to a user with a support type of IE)  \r\n'),
(393, 84, '2018\r\n Hello,\r\n\r\nI would like an interface that would allow us to search by CCM ID as well as IP address.  Both of these data fields are already linked to a specific client location.  Once the results are returned I would like to click on the location and see all open incident tickets as well as recent closed incident tickets from the previous 90 days. \r\n\r\n I would also like a single button to click that would create a new ticket under the specific client location that would automatically populate the following:\r\n\r\nSet the problem type to ''Incident and the problem subtype to ''circuit''.\r\n\r\nSet the End User Contact field to the primary preventive maintenance contact\r\n\r\nSet the end users contact number is the primary phone number for the primary preventative maintenance contact\r\n\r\nSet the end users email address to the email address of the primary preventive maintenance contact.\r\n\r\nWe would also like the ability to enter partial CCM IDs that would return multiple locations that match the partial information entered in the query.\r\n\r\nThis automation will save us a large quantity of time when working circuit tickets.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThanks\r\n\r\nGD'),
