(563, 125, 'EMAIL from Brian Russell:\r\nthread 1:\r\nDoes the CUCDM have APIs that we can leverage?  Our development team is looking to create an application that our clients will use that will allow them to make a voicemail pin change instead of our NOC being overloaded with these types of tickets.  I know we can use the Cisco API on Unity Connection to make this change but I was wondering if we should be doing that in CUCDM. Wouldnt CUCDM overwite a change that was done directly in Unity Connection?\r\nthread 2:\r\nI do not believe the API is technically supported in HCS but there is one. \r\nGenerally if you updated the Pin via CUC API, it would be out of sync with CUCDM and you could run into overwrite issues. I am trying to find someone who knows what we would have to do in order to allow you to set the PIN though the CUCDM Api. We might have to add anther software package to your system to make the API available. \r\n\r\nthread 3:\r\nFYI.  We may need to try getting the Voicemail PINs changed in CUCDM API so we are not taking a chance of sync issues.  I will followup with VOSS.'),
