(597, 97, 'FR #2822: The purpose of this document is to define the requirements for the population of the existing # Phones field in ITC and to add a new field called # Users.\r\n\r\n Currently, the # Phones field is populated with the total of a subset of user types which drives meaningless entries into the field. \r\n\r\nGoing forward the users want the field to be populated with the total of the Quantity Shipped of any NERs with the Equipment Type of IP Phone associated with that specific install record.\r\n\r\n # Users \r\nA new field entitled # Users is required that will accurately identify the number of users associated with a particular install. \r\nThis new field should have similar functionality of the existing # Phones field. \r\nThis field needs to be populated with the total of &quot;any&quot; billing user type listed below from the quote associated with the specific Install Record.\r\n Both of these fields need to be displayed in the Install Metrics Reports (Voice) similar to the current # Phones field. They should appear next to each other. \r\nPlease see attached requirements doc with screenshots. This request is critical to provide the VOC an accurate # of users being activated. The current reports display the inaccurate #Phones in the system today. )'),
