(605, 129, 'TESTING DIRECTIONS:\r\nSteps for recreating \r\n(Ticket #2606522: After the Cancel SA was in service for a month, the VOC decided they will need to have the Cancel SA generate Tickets rather than tasks to cancel users.)\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://itc.smoothstone.com/sap_quotes.phtml\r\nI. Sales &gt; Quote Management &gt; add + \r\n\r\nhttps://itc.smoothstone.com/sap/new_quote_step_1.php\r\nII. You''ll need a company and a user in that company that will have the appropriate billing_user_type for the particular service that you will soon cancel.*\r\n\r\n    A. Select the opportunity\r\n	B. select &quot;cancel&quot; for Quote type.\r\n	&quot;If I don''t mention certain steps then they are negligible&quot;\r\n	C.Company Status check existing\r\n	\r\n		1. Enter location\r\n		2. solution type\r\n		\r\n		/sap/new_quote_move_cancel.php\r\n	D. Step #4 Cancel Service\r\n	    in the available quantity you''ll need to see at least 1(user) for the particular service you are canceling.\r\n		cancel, add date, about three times...\r\n		\r\n	/sap_quotes_summary.phtml?filter[default][qid]=38765\r\n	E. At this point change the status to &quot;accepted&quot; \r\n	\r\n	\r\nIII. Sales &gt; Quote 2 Installs &gt; \r\n    A. search by your company name\r\n	B. select the &quot;continue&quot; column of the quote.\r\n	/sap_migrate.php?qid=38766\r\n	C. select the checkbox and click &quot;migrate&quot; button.\r\n	\r\n	A Ticket should have been sent to the VOC Disconnect Bin.\r\n	\r\n*I created a duplicate of my user account and assigned it to the &quot;test company&quot; I was using.\r\n Administration &gt; User Management \r\n Select that user ...\r\n in the &quot;Billing User Type&quot; select the service type you will cancel.\r\nMISSING PART:\r\n Finance &gt; Billing Details By Location &gt; Billing Services\r\n select the services that you will run test cancels on\r\n	\r\n	\r\n	'),
